.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-3-3::.
The people have 6 different jobs:  accountant, fisherman, doctor, social-worker, lawyer, architect
The people use 6 different means of transport: boat, car, jet-ski, ship, bike, helicopter
1. the person driving the ship is on the left or right of the accountant##3
2. the lawyer is on the left of the person driving the boat##1
3. the accountant is on the right of the person driving the car##1
4. the doctor is on the left or right of the person driving the car##3
5. the person driving the ship is on the far right##1
6. the social-worker is on the left or right of the person driving the jet-ski##3
7. the fisherman is between the social-worker and the doctor##2
8. the lawyer is on the right of the person driving the bike##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |     1      |     2      |      3      |     4     |    5     |     6     |
| Job         | social-worker | fisherman | doctor | lawyer | accountant  | architect    |
| Transport   | helicopter      | jet-ski  | bike  | car       | boat | ship |

