.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-3-14::.
There 6 different types of food: peas, lemon, kale, kiwi, papaya, zucchini
The people use 6 different means of transport: car, scooter, boat, subway, snowmobile, skateboard
 1. the person eating kale is on the right of the person eating lemon##1
 2. the person driving the boat is on the left or right of the person eating peas##3
 3. the person driving the skateboard is on the right of the person driving the car##1
 4. the person driving the snowmobile is on the left or right of the person eating zucchini##3
 5. the person eating kiwi is on the right of the person eating kale##1
 6. the person driving the skateboard is on the far left or far right##3
 7. the person eating papaya is between the person driving the subway and the person driving the scooter##2
 8. the person driving the car is the person eating kale##1
 9. the person driving the car is on the right of the person driving the snowmobile##1
10. the person eating peas is the person driving the scooter##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1    |   2    |    3     |     4     |     5      |   6    |
| Food        | peas  | papaya | zucchini | lemon | kale   | kiwi |
| Transport   | scooter | boat | subway    | snowmobile     | car | skateboard    |

